race.comment: OLD MATE HENRY (11) had showed plenty of talent but finally landed the knockout blow last time out, and did so in emphatic fashion. The step to 1800m looks perfect for him and the should get every chance from an inside barrier. Pike remains in the saddle and he can make it back-to-back wins. MISSISSIPPI DAWN (14) was very flat first-up but improved quickly last time out to get the job done. Up in grade today, but she's a progressive type who looks suited out to this trip now. CJP remains in the saddle and with improvement expected, she'll go close. MAXWHOOSHTAPIN (1) has returned in impressive fashion this campaign and up to 1800m is no issue. The draw is a query, though he does have good early speed and may be able to roll across from the draw. Going well enough to win this. PHAROAH SHOW (4) bolted in last start at Bunbury and can go on with the job. ROCK IN WONDER (5) can give a bold sight out in trip.
